body:
In commit "Handle reconciliation support announcement"

This conversion to decimal strings doesn't seem to match the BIP. I would think you'd do:

```c++
uint64_t salt1 = local_salt, salt2 = remote_salt;
if (salt1 > salt2) std::swap(salt1, salt2);
uint256 full_salt = (CHashWriter(SER_HASH, 0) << MakeSpan(RECON_STATIC_SALT) << salt1 << salt2).GetSHA256();
```

If the BIP is changed to use tagged hashes, you'd do

```c++
static const auto RECON_SALT_HASHER = TaggedHash(RECON_STATIC_SALT);
uint256 full_salt = (CHashWriter(RECON_SALT_HASHER) << salt1 << salt2).GetSHA256();
```

instead.

